05368nam a22008535i 9783110747331DE-B159720230228015514.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230228t20222022gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831107473317 a10.1515/97831107473312doi  a(DE-B1597)579755  a(OCoLC)1344541240  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aPOL0070002bisacsh0484pa320qDE-10100aComplementary Democracy :bThe Art of Deliberative Listening /ced. by Matt Qvortrup, Daniela Vancic. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (VI, 204 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aDemocracy in Times of Upheaval ,x2701-147X ;v400tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tIntroduction: Complementary Democracy – The New Frontier in Theory, Research, and Practice -- tFunctions of Deliberative Mini-Publics in Democratic Systems -- tParticipatory Budgeting: A Brief Introduction -- tRecall Elections -- tReferendums as Complementary Democracy -- tAgenda Initiatives in Comparative Context -- tTransnational Democracy’s Quest Across Borders -- tDigital Democracy: Past, Present, and Future -- tSortition in Current Democratic Regimes -- tSocial Movements as Democratic Actors -- tPerforming Democracy through Local Protests: The Case of Knitting Nannas Against Gas -- tDemocracy as Art -- tComplementary Democracy: Conclusions and the Way Ahead -- tAbout the Contributors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDemocracy is on the run, and elected governments are suffering from a legitimacy crisis. Legislatures are increasingly seen as unrepresentative. To give legitimacy to democratic government, experts argue that we need more democracy and more opportunities for direct citizen participation. Representative democracy needs to be complemented by forms of direct engagement, such as referendums, popular votes, the recall, citizens’ juries, eDemocracy, etc. This is what we term Complementary Democracy. In this book experts from the worlds of practice and theory come together to explain – and occasionally critique – these complements to representative democracy. The volume provides an invaluable starting point for anyone who wants to know more about the new directions of democratic governance, and hopes to inspire those who seek to build stronger democracies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh  aCitizens’ Juries.  aDeliberative Democracy.  aMini-publics.  aReferendum.1 aAdamopoulos, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelannoi, Gil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErcan, Selen A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFelicetti, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuller, Roslyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHendriks, Carolyn M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendez, Fernando, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendez, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPorta, Donatella della, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQvortrup, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQvortrup, Matt, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRíos, Greta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSetälä, Maija, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVancic, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVancic, Daniela, eeditor.4edt4http://id